Syntax: shadowform

Attempts to meld your body with the ambient shadows, granting an enhanced
form of the sneak effect. Shadow Form is a high-level stealth skill that
improves on basic sneak by providing a deeper concealment affect tied to
your Shadowform skill level rather than generic sneak.

Effects when successful:
  - Applies the AFF_SNEAK bitvector affect at your character level.
  - Duration scales with your level.
  - Any existing sneak affect is first removed before Shadowform is applied.

If the skill check fails, the attempt is announced to the room but no
benefit is gained.

Shadowform is available to rogue-line characters who have reached a
sufficient level in the Cipher, Assassin, or Warlock class lines.

Requirements:
  - Must have the Shadowform skill learned.
  - Must not be in a room that explicitly prevents hiding.

See also: shelp shadowform sneak hide disguise visible
